The paper deals with image fusion, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The use of deep learning-based methods and feature extraction also suggests the possibility of the paper belonging to the machine learning (cs.MM) or learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper specifically focuses on infrared and visible image fusion, which could place it in the sub-categories of image processing (cs.IR) or neural networks (cs.NE).
